Merge pull request #25 from jes5e/master

Added payment options component, a few small features, and several fixes
documentation of the payment optoins component
updated to latest rails 3.2.11 because of recently exposed security vulnerability in earlier versions
Fixed a bug where a string was being compared with a number
fixed a bug where backers count could be off in the tweet text on the order confirmation page
fixed a bug where backers count could be off on order confirmation page
a comment in the settings file was bad
Made a small change to make some wording configuration more flexible
added code so that port will be used if you are not in production mode so that you can test amazon flexible payments end to end in development
fixed a bug where the wrong price could get sent to amazon payments
fixed a query

made changes to Order model to reflect the fact that a site may use the new payment options component, resulting in orders of various dollar amounts, so revenue and goal percentage must be calculated differently

Making it so that files will get gzipped. Because the heroku cedar stack no longer uses nginx, gzip compression must be done by the app: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/http-routing#gzipped-responses
fixed a bug where sometimes in IE the video would auto start
Added html5 shiv so that the FAQ section will work in IE (it uses semantic tags like <details>)
Another IE fix.  Now the blue funding progress bar actually works in IE < 9.
Added html5 shiv so that the FAQ section will work in IE (it uses semantic tags like <details>)
fixed blue button in ie < 9.  Before it did not even show up
Fix for internet explorer.  The scss variables were enclosed in single quotes which made the variable names appear in the compiled css instead of the color values.
fix for payment optoins section so that the email controls do not overlap footer, even if you change the size of the footer
more style updates for payment options section
Added ability to have limited payment options that will count down as more people order them ("limited: x of y remaining"). When the limit is reached, the option becomes disabled
moved payment options configuration out of settings.yml and into a model
updated to use latest rails and removed dependency on therubyracer since heroku does not need it
some of the render statements werent using full paths and this causes problems when you try to use the layout from your own views not in the preorder directory
added classes for left and right float
Additional updates to styles on the payment options section
Additional updates to styles on the payment options section
fixed up styles on the payment options section
Updated some options in settings for clarity
removed some unused code
fixed the video link
Slight modification to the way the video placeholder image is displayed
added place holder image to show instead of video
added place holder image to show instead of video
more style changes for payment options component
fixed up styles for payment options component
since the default is to use amazon payments, then it makes sense for the default text to explain amazon payments - this text is now used by at least three different
fixed up some javascript
changed the placeholder text in the email field to make it more generic
fixed a typo
Made it so that when the "payment options" section is used on checkout, selecting a radio button makes the email field, and check-out button jump into view.
fixed: a setting was being referenced with an incorrect name
added an optional payment options section
